Tongwe Mountain. A mountain 2000 ft. high. Gneiss rocks with grey sandy loam. Covered with dry evergreen forest scrubby towards base and surrounded by coarse grassland. Forest - Celtis, Olyra latifolia everywhere, Erythrina sacleuxii, etc. The grassland consists of Roetboellia exaltata, Sorghum verticiflorum, Andropogon, etc. Dense shade in the more open parts of dry evergreen rain forest.
